^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The bidding was okay. By the Law, Nada should not bid 3H, because she has neither an extra heart nor a singleton spade. Eddy's bid is corrrect showing 5 spades and 6 points. Double shows exactly 4 spades. Now, Kerrie does have a problem. In general, it is not a good idea to let the opponents play at the two level when you both have a fit. But, her points are soft, 2 queens and the K in their suit. So, pass is acceptable and so is 3H. It is not clear whether they make 3H.|
