NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Eddy played it fine. On the surface you will lose 1 H, 1 or 2C, 1D, and 1 or 2 spades. You have as little as four losers and as much as six, depending on how lucky you are. Bascially, you have to hope the King of spades is onside, or the clubs can be played for one loser. You must ruff a diamond as you did. Nada made a very nice play underleading her Ace of clubs. Because even if Eddy has KJ, she makes him guess right away. |
PG| ***** 19 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, she should have followed it up with A and a low club to give Kerrie a ruff. If Kerrie started with KQx, does not matter, but if Eddy started with KJx, then it does matter. It turns out due to the spade spots Kerrie has a natural spade trick, but give Kerrie K76 of spades and it would have made a difference.|
