^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That was a good auction which we discussed. As to the play, it is true on many hands you do not draw trumps right away. The most common reason is because you need to ruff something in dummy before dummy is out of trumps. However, on this hand, the only thing that possibly needs to be ruffed in dummy is a spade. So, you can afford to draw 2 rounds of trump as there will still be at least one trump left in dummy. In general, you should draw trump ASAP unless you have a good reason not to. Otherwise, the opponents may end up ruffing your good tricks.|
PG| ***** 38 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On this hand in particular, you should suspect Eddy is short in clubs and although the club Queen has some merit as a lead, on this hand it is extremely helpful to declarer. After that lead declarer can now count 4 club tricks, as long as there are not excessive ruffs. So, it is even more imperative that trumps be drawn right away. As long as hearts are 3-2, (68%), the hand is easy once you get a club lead. An expert might figure out a way to increase the odds, but us mortals should be happy with a 68% contract. 
|
