NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Good job Roberta. We already had lots of comments on the play. I have a few minor comments on the bidding. After a 1N overcall, most people still play "|CP|8|AT|systems on|CP||AT|" by responder, as Ann did. So, 2D by Ann is still a heart transfer. 2C is Stayman, etc. Roberta should consider bidding 3H with her hand rather than 2H. In general, with 4 card support for a transfer, you should tend to bid 3 of the major. The only hand not to do it with is a 4-3-3-3 15 or weak 16 count. |
